  "translations": {
    "en": "He prohibited a woman from leaving her house without her husband's permission, for if she leaves, every angel in heaven and everything from the jinn and humans that passes her will curse her until she returns home. He prohibited a woman from adorning herself for other than her husband, for if she does, it is a right upon Allah to burn her in the Fire. He prohibited a woman from speaking to those other than her husband and close relatives more than five necessary words. He prohibited women from seeing one another without a garment between them. He prohibited a woman from telling another woman about intimate matters with her husband. He prohibited a man from having intercourse with his wife facing the qibla or on a busy road, for whoever does that, the curse of Allah, the angels, and all people is upon him. He prohibited a man from saying to another: 'Marry me to your sister so I may marry you to my sister.'",
